(H-) = -8.65 +/- 0.62 in\nHAT-P-41b's atmosphere, which is several orders of magnitude larger than\npredictions from equilibrium chemistry for a 1700 - 1950 K hot Jupiter. We show\nthat a combination of photochemical and collisional processes on hot\nhydrogen-dominated exoplanets can readily supply the necessary amount of H- and\nsuggest that such processes are at work in HAT-P-41b and many other hot Jupiter\natmospheres.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Oct 2020 18:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-20"}
